  "merge_count": 15,
  "source_runs": 4,
  "collected_notes": [
    "[nav]: The website uses a mega-menu for primary navigation which simplifies browsing tax types and digital services. Most interactive tasks (filing, checking balance) require authentication via Singpass.",
    "[auth]: IRAS has centralized its authentication via the myTax Portal, which utilizes Singapore's national digital identity platforms (Singpass for individuals and CorpPass for businesses). Consequently, all account registration and recovery flows are hosted on the Singpass domain rather than the IRAS domain itself.",
    "[commerce]: The IRAS website is a government tax agency portal and is not a commercial e-commerce site. While it facilitates tax payments (Stamp Duty, Property Tax, etc.) and offers fee-based services like 'Check Annual Value of Property' ($2.50 fee), it does not use a traditional commerce model. Specifically, there are no product listings, product detail pages for goods, 'add-to-cart' buttons, or a centralized shopping cart. Transactions are direct service or tax payments. Therefore, no commerce flows were identified.",
    "[support]: IRAS does not have a single 'Help Center' or 'Status' page link in the footer. Status information is typically communicated via banners or the login page (myTax Portal). Support is heavily categorized by tax type."
  ],
  "seed_url": "https://www.iras.gov.sg/",
